ol.li:
Define a CSS rule that changes the page property for the matching
            element.*[class ~= "two_columns"],
*[outputclass ~= "two_columns"]{ 
  page: two_column_page !important; 
}Use
            "class" attribute for the HTML transformation, "outputclass" for the direct
            transformation, or leave them both.The topics from the first level are
            using the chapter page. You must use !important
            because the built-in rules are more specific.

Define a page
          layout.@page two_column_page {
  column-count: 2;
}
